"t_title108","自由廣場》綠營奇兵",NA," 自由時報APP看新聞又抽獎 ◎ 黃子祥        如果民進黨要賴清德去選台北市長，我反對！理由只有一個，既然做了行政院長，就認真地把行政院長做好，這對台灣藍綠都好。民進黨支持者不能拿國家大政當實習材料，只會跟著政客想贏贏贏！政治有比輸贏更重要的價值好嗎？    至於陳菊，我沒有意見，她現在那個位置說重要就重要、說不重要就不重要。倒是對她去擔任蘇貞昌競選總幹事，讓人覺得不妥，有黨政不分的嫌疑。    其實小英如果能從綠營，或者台派（台灣優先派）去挑人，而不只是從民進黨內挑人的話，我認為林昶佐和鄭麗君是好牌，是最有希望贏得台北市長選戰的人。不過政治上的盤算我不懂，林昶佐和鄭麗君的意願我也不清楚，純粹是我個人日常接觸到、聽到的一些聲音吧！    （作者任職金融業，台北市民）        ◎ 王伯仁        根據新台灣國策智庫的最新民調，台北市長選舉如果「三腳督」，柯文哲、丁守中分居一、二，民進黨可能人選（賴清德、陳菊、姚文智）都居第三。此民調有一大盲點，即綠營至今尚未提名確定，用「可能人選」參加民調，當然有不確定模糊感，統計上有相當缺失，如果提名確定以後，民調結果應會大不同。    不過，賴清德和陳菊不一定適合現階段參選台北市長，就如蔡英文以總統之尊，現在跳下來選台北市長，也不一定有贏面，時空因素而已。至於準備已久的姚文智立委，聲勢一直拉不上來，有一定程度的事實，也一定有客觀上的理由，所以無法有效凝聚綠營及中間選民的關注，民調屢屢偏低，就如新北市吳秉叡立委一樣。    但看是「山窮水盡疑無路」，但「柳暗花明又一村」，不必動到行政院長和總統府秘書長，文化部長鄭麗君正是負分變正分的關鍵。她形象清新、睿智、冷靜、大方、年輕、魅力<U+22EF>，條件比日本東京都知事小池百合子更好，她戴斗笠參加過反核千里苦行，毅力體力不在話下，對年輕一族的親近度，比柯Ｐ更有吸引力（她參加創設哲學星期五），更不用說丁叔叔了。    民進黨有這塊瑰寶，如果出來，當選率遠比柯Ｐ和丁高，只是選市長並不在她既有人生規劃中，但也有人說，戰士沒有選擇戰場的權利，果真如此，可惜的是我們會少了一位優質的文化部長。    （作者為資深新聞從業人員）        ◎ 黃秀梨        根據新台灣國策智庫最新民調，台北市長部分，若以姚文智、賴清德和陳菊，分別對上柯文哲以及丁守中，柯文哲不論在哪個組合，均居於民調之首。包括：柯文哲（32.9%）vs.丁守中（30.4%）vs.陳菊（24.0%）；柯文哲（34.0%）vs.丁守中（30.4%）vs.賴清德（22.8%）；柯文哲（39.4%）vs.丁守中（33.5%）vs.姚文智（13.8%）。民調的結果陳菊跟賴清德比姚文智都高，但因為賴清德是行政院長，如果跳下來選市長將影響內閣穩定性，而另一天王陳菊民調數字比姚要高出10趴，且當初令人感動的「戰士沒有選擇戰場的權利」亦言猶在耳，為何輕言棄選？    （作者為退休高中教師，彰化縣民）  新聞送上來！ 快加入APP、LINE好友 iOS Android APP下載 LINE好友","51"
"t_title109","《TAIPEI TIMES》 Hou You-yi, Ko leading favorability polls, while Chen, Lim not running
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月12日•星期二•戊戌年四月廿九日"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  CATCH-ALL NAME: Respondents in a poll were given four scenarios for the Taipei race, and Ko Wen-je came out on top in each of them, the Taiwan Brain Trust said By Lee I-chia / Staff reporter Former New Taipei City deputy mayor Hou You-yi （侯友宜） and Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je （柯文哲） have the highest favorability ratings among major political figures and candidates running in the Nov. 24 nine-in-one elections, a poll released yesterday by the Taiwan Brain Trust showed. The poll surveyed eligible voters in the six special municipalities to gauge the approval and favorability ratings of political figures and candidates. As the municipalities’ residents account for about 70 percent of the nation’s population, the poll also gauged the approval ratings of President Tsai Ing-wen （蔡英文） and Premier William Lai （賴清德）. According to the poll, 56.5 percent of respondents disapproved of Tsai’s performance, while 28.8 percent approved. Lai had an approval rating of 39.3 percent and a disapproval rating of 39 percent, the survey found. Respondents were given a list of 18 major political figures and mayoral candidates, and were asked to select who they favored. They were allowed to choose multiple names. Hou was the only figure favored by more than half of respondents, with a favorability rating of 50.2 percent. He was closely followed by Ko （48.5 percent）, Lai （47.9 percent）, Taichung Mayor Lin Chia-lung （林佳龍） （43.8 percent） and New Taipei City Mayor Eric Chu （朱立倫） （43.5 percent）. Tsai, who is the Democratic Progressive Party （DPP） chairperson, ranked eighth with a favorability rating of 35.6 percent, while Chinese Nationalist Part （KMT） Chairman Wu Den-yih （吳敦義） ranked 15th with a favorability rating of 18.6 percent. Ko had the highest support rate in each of the four scenarios presented to the respondents for the Taipei mayoral election: running against KMT candidate Ting Shou-chung （丁守中） with no DPP candidate; running against Ting and DPP Legislator Pasuya Yao （姚文智）; against Ting and Presidential Office Secretary-General Chen Chu （陳菊）, and against Ting and Lai. Even though some DPP politicians have criticized Ko, and his favorability rating has fallen to 43.3 percent in Taipei, he still received higher support rates — ranging from 44.3 to 53.4 percent — in the other five municipalities, Trend Survey and Research Co general manager Wu Shih-chang （吳世昌） said. If Ko were to run for president in 2020 and received only 5 percent of the vote, it could still result in Tsai losing the election, he said. People aged 20 to 39 view Ko most favorably, those 40 to 59 years old prefer Hou, and people older than 60 favor Lai, Wu said. “Ko has a high support rate and can attract voters from the pan-blue and pan-green camps, as well as neutral voters and even New Power Party （NPP） supporters,” Ketagalan Institute president Chin Heng-wei （金恆煒） said, adding that the DPP faces a challenge in party politics, as its supporters seem less passionate about and alienated from the party. Taoyuan Mayor Cheng Wen-tsan （鄭文燦） has the highest approval rating among mayors at 77.5 percent, followed by Lin in Taichung （55.7 percent）, who rose to No. 2 after Chen last month left her post as Kaohsiung mayor. Chen ranked No. 2 in the previous poll released in December last year. The poll was conducted between Monday and Thursday last week through telephone interviews and a stratified proportional sampling of 4,891 adult residents of the six municipalities. It has a confidence level of 95 percent and a margin of error of 1.4 percent. CHEN, LIM NOT TO RUN Chen meanwhile yesterday denied that she would run for Taipei mayor, after she was viewed by many DPP supporters as a strong candidate, adding that her duty is to assist the president in pushing forward reforms. NPP Legislator Freddy Lim （林昶佐） yesterday said in a radio interview that he would also not run for Taipei mayor, because he does not want to split the pro-local and progressive vote, adding that he would not seek an alliance with Ko either. 新聞來源：TAIPEI TIMES Presidential Office Secretary-General Chen Chu, center, and Democratic Progressive Party prospective Kaohsiung mayoral candidate Chen Chi-mai, second right, attend a promotional event for fruit grown in Kaohsiung at the Legislative Yuan in Taipei yesterday.
